HEADWORD: Xylophaga
<hw>Xy*loph"a*ga</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Xylophagous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of
marine bivalves which bore holes in wood. They are allied to
Pholas.</def>⟦br⟧
